    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "test: cover unused mempool space in coins cache limit",
    "user": {
      "login": "w0xlt",
      "id": 94266259,
      "node_id": "U_kgDOBZ5jkw",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/94266259?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/w0xlt",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/w0xlt/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "This PR adds a unit test for `Chainstate::GetCoinsCacheSizeState()`.\r\n\r\n`Chainstate::GetCoinsCacheSizeState()` calculates when the UTXO/coins cache is too large and should be flushed. Part of that calculation includes unused `-maxmempool` space. For example, if the mempool limit is 300 MiB but the mempool is mostly empty, some of that unused space can be counted toward the coins cache limit.\r\n\r\nThe existing `validation_flush_tests.cpp` test checks this calculation by calling:\r\n\r\n```c++\r\nchainstate.GetCoinsCacheSizeState(MAX_COINS_BYTES, max_mempool_size_bytes)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis new test checks the no-argument call:\r\n\r\n```c++\r\nchainstate.GetCoinsCacheSizeState()\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat is the call used by validation code during normal operation.\r\n\r\nThe test grows the coins cache above the coins-only limit, then checks that:\r\n- calling the explicit helper with `max_mempool_size_bytes=0` reports `CRITICAL`\r\n- calling the normal no-argument method does not report `CRITICAL`, because it includes unused mempool space\r\n\r\nThis makes sure future refactors do not accidentally drop unused mempool space from the normal cache-size calculation.",
